content: The game is great for playing with friends and family, but the screen will glitch during 70% of your games and you have no choice but to quit and start over. Cand be very frustrating.
Only wish it had some customization for the colors.

It glitches often. Also, I find it strange the same real-like picture will be used as a profile picture by two different players that you are playing a hand with yet i don't see these pictures as an option for you to choose from as your avatar.

As a longtime "Spite & Malice" / "Cat and Mouse" / Skip-Bo(R) player, I'd really like to give this app five stars. But I can only give v1.1 three stars owing to numerous bugs and design issues. TOP BUGS (1) When playing cards, they can get 'stuck' in odd positions and unplayable; forcing you to have to play a different card. (2) Frequent network dropouts to game server, possibly due to relative age of my HTC Desire. But I'd pay the $4.99 all over again to play with friends and fos alike online.

As I was playing the game online it got me put then right back into the game then it crashed and now I have to go back into the app play again. Not good if you have to play again with the online. I download the latest version a few days ago and now I'm not happy with the version plus I paid for the old version and this one after playing a few days. Sry would like my money back.
Way too glitchy. Can barely get through a single game.
App hangs up when trying to create game to play with friends
Barely let's me connect to games and kicks me during games even when I have stable connection.

Hopeless. Game is glitching out. Either one gets the white screen of death or your cards are disappearing. Games with 25+ cards are unplayable since it's impossible to close the app and join the same game. Would not recommend anyone to buy this.
It is a great game. How can I use my own picture?? I don't like using a picture someone else is using.

I had the original skip-bo. I paid for ads but opened to be blasted with ads. Telling me about the new app they released. I choose to buy it due to the fact I couldn't remove ads on that version. What I paid for was the exact same product but laggy as all hell. I should have got the game free or been allowed to keep the old version without ads. Kinda shallow to undo my ad free purchase and give me nothing in return.
